text.section:
The legislative body of any city of the home rule class may by ordinance:
Provide the city with water; establish, regulate and control public cisterns, hydrants and reservoirs, together with extensions and appurtenances thereto, within or without the limits of the city, for fire protection and the use and convenience of its inhabitants;
Provide for the enforcement of said regulations for the health, welfare and well-being of its inhabitants.
